<div id="main-article" class="article-content retro-folders">
<p><em>Isaac Asimov's Wonderful Worlds of Science Fiction</em> is an anthology book series put together by <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/IsaacAsimov" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/IsaacAsimov">Isaac Asimov</a> and editors <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/MartinHGreenberg" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/MartinHGreenberg">Martin H. Greenberg</a>, and <a class="createlink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/CharlesGWaugh" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/CharlesGWaugh">Charles G. Waugh</a> to showcase noteworthy <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ScienceFiction" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ScienceFiction">Science Fiction</a> short stories. It spanned ten books from 1983 to 1990. Each book focused on a specific subject and featured an introduction by Asimov discussing the volume's topic. Starting with the sixth book, <em>Tin Stars</em>, the series began having a unified visual theme in terms of cover art. See also <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/FantasticCreatures" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/FantasticCreatures">Fantastic Creatures</a></em></p><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_1"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_1'); })</script></div></div><p></p><hr><h2>Works collected in #1 <em>Intergalactic Empires</em> (1983):</h2><ul><li> "<a class="createlink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/ChaliceOfDeath" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/ChaliceOfDeath">Chalice of Death</a>" by <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/RobertSilverberg" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/RobertSilverberg">Robert Silverberg</a> (1957)</li><li> "<a class="createlink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheManWhoWasntHome" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheManWhoWasntHome">Orphan of the World</a>" by <a class="createlink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/LloydBiggleJr" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/LloydBiggleJr">Lloyd Biggle, Jr.</a> (1972)</li><li> "<a class="createlink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/DownToTheWoodsOfMen" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/DownToTheWoodsOfMen">Down to the Woods of Men</a>" by <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/AlexeiPanshin" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/AlexeiPanshin">Alexei Panshin</a> (1963)</li><li> "<a class="createlink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/MinistryOfDisturbance" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/MinistryOfDisturbance">Ministry of Disturbance</a>" by <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/HBeamPiper" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/HBeamPiper">H. Beam Piper</a> (1958)</li><li> "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/BlindAlley" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/BlindAlley">Blind Alley</a>" by Isaac Asimov (1945)</li><li> "<a class="createlink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/APlanetNamedShayol" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/APlanetNamedShayol">A Planet Named Shayol</a>" by <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/CordwainerSmith" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/CordwainerSmith">Cordwainer Smith</a> (1961)</li><li> "<a class="createlink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Diabologic" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Diabologic">Diabologic</a>" by <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/EricFrankRussell" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/EricFrankRussell">Eric Frank Russell</a> (1955)</li><li> "<a class="createlink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/FightingPhilosopher" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/FightingPhilosopher">Fighting Philosopher</a>" by <a class="createlink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/EBCole" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/EBCole">E.B. Cole</a> (1954)</li><li> "<a class="createlink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/HonorableEnemies" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/HonorableEnemies">Honorable Enemies</a>" by <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/PoulAnderson" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/PoulAnderson">Poul Anderson</a> (1951)</li></ul><hr><hr><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_2"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_2'); })</script></div></div><h2>Works collected in #2 <em>The Science Fictional Olympics</em> (1984):</h2><ul><li> "<a class="createlink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/RunToStarlight" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/RunToStarlight">Run to Starlight</a>" by <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/GeorgeRRMartin" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/GeorgeRRMartin">George R. R. Martin</a> (1974)</li><li> "<a class="createlink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheMickeyMouseOlympics" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheMickeyMouseOlympics">The Mickey Mouse Olympics</a>" by <a class="createlink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/TomSullivan" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/TomSullivan">Tom Sullivan</a> (1979)</li><li> "<a class="createlink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/DreamFighter" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/DreamFighter">Dream Fighter</a>" by <a class="createlink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/BobShaw" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/BobShaw">Bob Shaw</a> (1977)</li><li> "<a class="createlink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheKokodWarriors" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheKokodWarriors">The Kokod Warriors</a>" by <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/JackVance" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/JackVance">Jack Vance</a> (1952)</li><li> "<a class="createlink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/GettingThroughUniversity" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/GettingThroughUniversity">Getting Through University</a>" by <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/PiersAnthony" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/C